cs.DL, cs.MS, cs.SE, cs.CE, cs.SC 

The paper discusses the OpenDreamKit project, which is focused on developing open-source mathematical software systems. This makes it likely to fall under the following sub-categories: 

- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): The project aims to support the ecosystem of open-source mathematical software systems, which could be seen as a type of digital library. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the development of a toolkit for setting up Virtual Research Environments for mathematical research projects. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The project involves developing a flexible toolkit for research groups, which could involve software engineering practices. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper mentions that the toolkit will be used for research projects in pure mathematics and applications, which could fall under this sub-category. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The focus on mathematical software systems and Virtual Research Environments suggests that this paper could be relevant to the sub-category of Symbolic Computation.
